File: Gauteng MEC for Education Panyaza Lesufi. JOHANNESBURG - Electronic equipment has been stolen from a Klipfontein View school in Midrand. It's the second robbery at the school in two months. WATCH: Lesufi: school robberies becoming the norm Gauteng Education MEC Panyaza Leufi confirmed the incident on social media. In January, Menzi Primary School was burgled. Armed robbers also targeted Edenvale High School in February.